Title: 4 Film Favorites: Elvis Presley Classics (Charro, It Happened at the World's Fair, Jailhouse Rock: Deluxe Edition, Stay Away, Joe)

reviewText: This DVD includes four of Elvis Presley's movies: 1957's Jailhouse Rock, 1963's It Happened at the World's Fair, 1968's Stay Away Joe, and 1969's Charro!Jailhouse Rock is the best out of the bunch.  It was Elvis' third film and includes an outstanding collection of early rock songs such as "Jailhouse Rock", "Treat Me Nice", and "Young and Beautiful".  Elvis stars as an ex-con who makes it big as a singer after his release from prison.  Tragically, Elvis' co-star, Judy Tyler, was killed in an automobile accident a few weeks after the film was completed.  Elvis was so upset by the loss that he refused to ever watch the completed film. In 2004, this film was selected for preservation in the United States National Film Registry as being deemed "culturally, historically, or aesthetically significant."It Happened at the World's Fair is lighthearted musical comedy that was typical of Elvis movies.Stay Away, Joe is a modern western, comedy-drama with Elvis staring as Navajo Indian trying to help out his family and people.Charro! is a serious, more mature, western drama and one of Elvis' last films, and his only role that didn't feature the him singing on-screen (he does sing the theme song but it is off-screen).  This is a typical late-60's western and is not a bad movie.  It is my second favorite in this collection.If you like Elvis Presley movies, you should enjoy this DVD.
summary: One of the better sets of Elvis movies
Title: 4 Film Favorites: Elvis Presley Classics (Charro, It Happened at the World's Fair, Jailhouse Rock: Deluxe Edition, Stay Away, Joe)

reviewText: Why is it that so many movie collections like this are NOT among the best films of some actor, yet packaged as though they were? Of the four on here, only "Jailhouse Rock" is really among his best films, although "It Happened At the World's Fair" is a decent movie too, though not one of his best. Both of those films have quite good songs in them, although the songs in World's Fair are more ballad and pop oriented. "Charro" has him singing only the title song, although I think that western is a little better than the usually very negative reviews that it gets. At least "Charro" and "Stay Away, Joe" from the late-60s are a departure from the stale "beach movie" types of films Elvis was stuck in by the mid-60s, yet "Stay Away, Joe" is VERY strange and several characters in it are an insult to Native Americans. So unless you're either an Elvis completest or you already know you like these films, stick to his best:King Creole,Wild in the Country,Follow That Dream,Jailhouse Rock (Deluxe Edition),Loving You,Flaming Star,Speedway, andViva Las Vegas (Deluxe Edition). My favorite collection of Elvis movies, although it has some weak ones in it too, isElvis Presley - The Signature Collection (It Happened at the World's Fair / Speedway / Spinout / Harum Scarum / Jailhouse Rock / Viva Las Vegas).
summary: Only one of these is among Elvis's best

reviewText: How can a review of Elvis Presley movies be made? His movies are entertaining with poor acting and with poor plots. He sings well and the movies are so lighthearted that who cares if the acting and script is not the best.I liked Buddy Holly and did not like the Beatles. But, I like Elvis songs so I enjoy his movies. I am not at all critical because he could not act. John Wayne could not act and neither could Robert Redford. We have a tendency to like what we are supposed to like. Nobody can say that Denzel Washington is a bad actor. I say he is mediocre at best. Now Gene Hackman and Kevin Costner can act. So I rate this Elvis 4 pack at 5 stars because I enjoyed all 4 movies and watched them all the way through. However, it took me two nights on one of them. I got tired.
summary: Elvis is always entertaining and these 4 in one package is a 5 atar bargain

reviewText: I'm glad there were three other movies along with Stay Away Joe.  I have loved Elvis since 1956, but it was hard to watch this.  Now that I'm not a teenager, I need more substance from a movie.  However Jailhouse Rock and Charro were not in the general mold of most Elvis movies.  Both were great, and to me Charro is his best ever.  It made me think there was something to him besides a handsome face and a wonderful voice.  I believe he could have been a fine actor given a chance at better roles.
summary: Stay Away from Stay Away Joe
Title: 4 Film Favorites: Elvis Presley Classics (Charro, It Happened at the World's Fair, Jailhouse Rock: Deluxe Edition, Stay Away, Joe)

reviewText: With the exception of the classic Jailhouse Rock, we have what might be called Elvis' "lost" movies, meaning one quality Hollywood Musical which has been overlooked and two which deserve the overlooking.JAILHOUSE ROCK (**** 1/2*) is the 1957 must-see: Elvis' acting is a quantum leap forward from his second movie (first starring role in Loving You); the script is excellent and so is the music. We have a serious, credible drama (outside the "rock and Roll movie" genre) with songs. No breaking into a song, a la Bing Crosby, 1935.IT HAPPENED AT THE WORLD'S FAIR (*** 1/2*) along with Viva Las Vegas, a solid movie actually filmed on location, which has survived decades of opprobium from critics and fans who obviously walked away after the first 3 songs. I purchased this CD set for this movie and my newfound interest in Elvis "movie versions" of the soundtrack album.Fans, if you love Elvis' voice, then dig it on "Take Me To The Fair". Another example of what the engineers could do in drowning out his great closing long notes. There are some outstanding scenes with the child actress - she is excellent. There's no cloying sentiment - the Director was able to evoke real sympathy for the orphaned child, suddenly finding herself in the "adult" world of gambling, booze, and struggle. A very progressive little piece of film history.Elvis really kicks up his heels here, literally in two of the best fight scenes I've ever seen - too bad someone decided to (unnecessarily) speed up the frames.I daresay that Elvis is every bit as good in this light flick as he was in the haevy Western drama, Flaming Star. Art Direction is fine, so is the lighting, as Elvis never looked greater.What stops me ftrom issuing a ***** is that the film has2-3 too many songs and it does sag in the middle.STAY AWAY, JOE (**) Here's a marginal ** only in deference to the decision to bring Elvis "up to date" as an actor...getting away from malibu Beach and placing him out in Sedona, arizona. Good Presley performance and terrific songs wasted (I know about "Dominic, The Impotent Bull"). It's been widely and accurately observed that the frivolous stereotyping of Native Americans depiction is a solid reason to....click back to Jailhouse Rock.CHARRO (*) Sorry, fans, this is an awful movie. Elvis is very unconvincing as  a former gang member who went straight only to be confronted by said aggeregate. The situation of a "pacifist" Sheriff, willing to let his town go down for the sake of Peace, is poorly realized. The well-known backstory is that the Director was told to keep things nice and light - unlike the original idea which would have Presley getting down and dirty. Gotta say it - this one *needed* some silly songs!

reviewText: I enjoy Elvis movies because I grew up with them. That being said, this package contains 3 of his better movies and Stay Away,Joe.Jailhouse Rock is a classic, and Charro! is a good old-fashioned western and Elvis does some very good acting although the Elvis fans will miss his singing in it, 'cause he doesn't.(Other than the Title Song). It Happened at the World's Fair is one of his many throw away scripts that he made so many of, but I enjoy it. Stay Away, Joe, while funny at times, is not his best work.
